<h2>Election of Putin</h2>
Exactly 25 years ago, on March 26, 2000, the Russians elected President for the first time former Kgb agent Vladimir Putin, > who arrived at the highest office in the country after only a few months spent in politics. At that time Russia was suffering the consequences of the default and was submerged with debts. Inflation was 36.5%, unemployment was 13%. A Russian on three lived below the poverty line > remembers today the Tass state agency. The urn candidates were 11, but already at the beginning of the election campaign, Putin was candidate number 1 after - when he was still primer - he was appointed head of state interim by his predecessor Boris Eltsin>, in the dramatic speech to the nation of 31 December 1999. With an audience of 68.7%, that March 26 voted for Putin 52.9% of voters.
