In the cast of the Putinian model, Rachman inserts in his book politicians born in very different contexts: from Recep Tayyip Erdogan in Turkey to Xi Jinping in China and Narendra Modi in India.> But the strong man's putinian model has also waited in more structured democracies, such as Israel with Benjamin Netanyahu, the United Kingdom with Boris Johnson to the United States with Donald Trump. "The cancellation of a clear distinction between democratic and authoritarian leadership has been the key objective of strong men for decades," Rachman warned. A statement never today.
